Verify Image Tag
SSH into the host where your Docker registry is running and run:

bash
Copy
Edit
curl -u admin:admin https://sd-wv58-kflz.nam.nsroot.net:5000/v2/_catalog --insecure
Then check all available tags for this image:

bash
Copy
Edit
curl -u admin:admin https://sd-wv58-kflz.nam.nsroot.net:5000/v2/cdp-private/cloudera/redhat8/postgresql-10/tags/list --insecure
Look for 1-215. If it's missing, proceed to the next step.

2. Load the Correct Image
Go to the directory where you have the .tar.gz image files (you mentioned /docker2/1.5.4-h10/images) and run:

bash
Copy
Edit
gunzip postgresql-10_1-215.tar.gz
docker load -i postgresql-10_1-215.tar
docker tag <loaded-image-id> sd-wv58-kflz.nam.nsroot.net:5000/cdp-private/cloudera/redhat8/postgresql-10:1-215
docker push sd-wv58-kflz.nam.nsroot.net:5000/cdp-private/cloudera/redhat8/postgresql-10:1-215
Make sure TLS and htpasswd are working as expected for pushing to the registry.

3. Restart the Failing Pod
After pushing the image successfully:

bash
Copy
Edit
oc delete pod cdp-embedded-db-0 -n xyz
The StatefulSet will recreate it and should now pull the image correctly.
